
[1]novice

   NOV'ICE, n. [L. from new.]

   1. One who is new in any business; one unacquainted or unskilled; one
   in the rudiments; a beginner.

   I am young, a novice in the trade.

   2. One that has entered a religious house but has not taken the vow; a
   probationer.

   3. One newly planted in the church, or one newly converted to the
   Christian faith. 1 Timothy 3.
